DESCRIPTION:

We have determined an estimate of degree 1 gravity coefficients based on
ocean and atmospheric models and GRACE coefficients for degrees 2 and higher
[Swenson et al., 2008]. Data from the new Release-05 data have been used.

The coefficients in this file represent the degree 1 gravity coefficients that should be added to the GSM coefficients to correct for geocenter motion,
relative to the modeled atmosphere and ocean degree 1 coefficients.
The coefficients have been normalized  using the GRACE standards. 
To use for land applications or to compute global ocean mass, use
these coefficients along with GRACE GSM coefficients for degrees 2 and higher,
along with a Degree 1 Love number (k1) = 0.021.

For ocean applications, add the degree 1 values found in the ocean bottom
pressure product (GAD) to these values. If you are interested in the 
full ocean, land, atmosphere geocenter, add the degree 1 values of the 
atmosphere/ocean product (GAC) to these values. 

Data format is similar to that for GSM, GAD, and GAC files distributed by 
PODAAC, where the last two columns reflect the start and end times for the 
GSM file in the format of <year><month><day>.

from a combination of GRACE and ocean model output, J. Geophys. Res.,
